{#-
  exemplar_present.jinja (English)
  HumanMessage body that presents the exemplars (full scripts OR single-utterance examples).
  Domain-neutral (werewolf / HiddenBench). The reply (ack or analysis) is supplied by the
  following AIMessage, so this does NOT ask the model to acknowledge.
  Expects:
    scenario_bodies (list[str]), scenario_count (int)
    exemplar_kind ('scripts' | 'utterances')
-#}
{% set _kind = exemplar_kind | default('scripts') -%}
{% if _kind == 'utterances' -%}
Below are individual utterance examples observed in good discussions ({{ scenario_count }} set(s)). Use them as a reference for phrasing, pacing, and how to raise points when you speak.
{%- elif _kind == 'situations' -%}
Below are situation/scene phrasing examples from good discussions ({{ scenario_count }} set(s)): short lines suited to particular moments. Use them as a reference for how to phrase yourself in each kind of situation when you speak.
{%- else -%}
Below are complete records of good discussions, start to finish ({{ scenario_count }} transcript(s)). Use them as a reference for how a discussion you are about to join should proceed — its flow and the texture of the utterances.
{%- endif %}

--- begin ---

{% for body in scenario_bodies %}
{{ body }}

---

{% endfor %}
--- end ---
{% if request_analysis and _kind == 'scripts' %}

Having read the above, please summarize your observations and return them:
- How the discussion develops — how it progresses round by round.
- The points that make a script as readable and engaging as these references.
{%- endif %}
